<h1 class="hero-h">Do I Need an AI Strategy? <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">You need a roadmap, not a strategy.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">A surprisingly common question, with a surprisingly clear answer. Most mid-market B2B companies do not need a 30-page AI strategy. They need a one-page AI roadmap with three workflows and a named owner. Strategy decks delay action; roadmaps cause it.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">No — most $5M-$50M B2B companies do not need a formal AI strategy. They need a one-page AI roadmap with 3 prioritized workflows, a named owner, and a budget. The strategy is implicit in the roadmap; making it explicit usually delays action.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">The difference between a strategy and a roadmap</h2><p class="body">A <strong>strategy</strong> answers: where will AI take us, why, and how does it fit our broader plan. A <strong>roadmap</strong> answers: what specific workflows do we change in the next 90 days, who owns each, what does success look like, what is the budget.</p><p class="body">At $5M-$50M, the strategy is usually obvious ("use AI to increase output per person without hiring") and the roadmap is the hard part. Producing a 30-page strategy document is usually procrastination disguised as planning.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When a real AI strategy is warranted</h2><ul class="ul"><li>You are a 500+ person enterprise considering centralized AI investments across many business units.</li><li>You are evaluating whether to build proprietary AI products (not just internal tools).</li><li>You operate in a regulated environment where AI usage requires formal governance frameworks.</li><li>You are raising capital and investors want to see an AI thesis.</li></ul><p class="body">If none of these apply, skip the strategy. Build the roadmap.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What to do instead</h2><ol class="ol"><li>Run the <a href="/ai-readiness-checklist" style="color:#00C853;">25-question AI readiness checklist</a>. Fix the foundation gaps you find.</li><li>Use the <a href="/ai-use-case-prioritization-framework" style="color:#00C853;">use case prioritization framework</a> to pick the top 3 workflows.</li><li>Follow the <a href="/ai-implementation-roadmap-template" style="color:#00C853;">90-day implementation roadmap template</a>.</li><li>Name a single owner. Give them protected time. Ship the first workflow in 4 weeks.</li></ol></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is an AI strategy the same as digital transformation?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Digital transformation is a broader, slower initiative. AI strategy is one component. Both terms are over-used and over-scoped at mid-market.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Should the CEO write the AI strategy?</h3><p class="faq-qa">The CEO should write the one-paragraph statement of intent. The roadmap and ownership should be delegated to the AI lead (with CEO check-ins).</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How long should an AI roadmap be?</h3><p class="faq-qa">One page. If yours is longer, you are mixing planning with theater. Cut until it fits.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do we need to define an AI vision statement?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Vision statements are post-rationalization. Ship 3 workflows; the vision will become clear from what worked.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Can our existing strategy consultant write our AI strategy?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Probably not well. Strategy consultants who do not implement will produce a strategy that nobody knows how to execute. Hire someone who has shipped AI workflows, not just thought about them.</p></div>
</div></section>

